bilingual.source: Take a tent and a rain jacket.
You will not sleep in a tent.
We put up the tent and fell asleep.
bilingual.target: 我们搭起帐篷然后睡着了。

bilingual.source: This is a photo of Dad and his tent.
bilingual.target: 这是爸爸和他的帐篷的照片。

bilingual.source: We put up a tent and cooked outside.
bilingual.target: 我们搭了帐篷并在外面做饭。

bilingual.source: Could you please bring a tent, Liu Chang?
We live in a beautiful and strong tent.
bilingual.target: 我们住在一个漂亮而坚固的帐篷里。

list.abstract: 是英文单词，读音有：英[tent]美[tɛnt]，翻译为：帐篷; 帐篷状物; 塞子。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa, George, this is the tent I had when I was a little boy! Daddy? How are you going to make that into a tent?
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩琪，乔治，这个帐篷是我小时候用过的！爸爸？你是怎么把这个搭成一顶帐篷的？

yingyinNormal.en: So he can show me how about the tent then, right?
yingyinNormal.zh: 到时候他就会教我搭帐篷了，对吧?

yingyinNormal.en: What about one big tent right in front of the Capitol?
yingyinNormal.zh: 在国会大门口支个大帐篷怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: And the brave cowboy Pedro was alone in his tent. But he couldn't sleep, because something was outside the tent. Was it a wild animal?
yingyinNormal.zh: 勇敢的牛仔佩德罗独自一人呆在帐篷里。他一点都睡不着，因为有什么东西正在帐篷的外面。是不是有野兽在外面呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and her friends are putting up their tents. Children, you must each find a partner to share your tent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇和朋友们搭起了帐篷。每一个人要找一个伙伴一起共用一个帐篷。

yingyinNormal.en: Mummy Pig, Peppa and George are sleeping in the tent. Daddy Pig is sleeping outside, under the stars. I love camping!
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪妈妈，佩琪和乔治睡在帐篷里。猪爸爸在帐篷外的星空下睡着了。我真喜欢宿营 ！

yingyinNormal.en: All right. Here it goes. I never actually built a tent before. There. I said it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不管了，告诉你，我根本没搭过帐篷，哇，解脱了。

yingyinNormal.en: Let's have a story in the tent. I can tell a story. Make it scary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 让我们一起到帐篷里讲故事吧。我们来讲一个故事吧。讲一个恐怖的故事。

yingyinNormal.en: Are they ready for these? Give me those. James! Could you take these to the tent, please?
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以放这些了吗？给我吧，詹姆斯，麻烦把这些放到帐篷里？

yingyinNormal.en: What's that? Grandpa Pig is putting up a big stripy tent in his garden. It's the circus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是什么？猪爷爷在花园里支起一个条纹帐篷。这是个马戏团。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, why didn't you ask your dad how to build a tent? I don't think he wants to talk about this stuff.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你为什么不跟你爸学习搭帐篷呢? 他不会跟我说这个的。

yingyinNormal.en: Rebecca, you said you'd share with me. Oh, yes. Emily, who you are going to share tent with? Zoe. Okay. Good, now you can share with me. OKay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瑞贝卡，你已经答应了和我用一个。噢，是的。艾米丽你要和谁共用一个帐篷呢？我选佐伊。好的。好了，我们可以共用帐篷了。好的。

yingyinNormal.en: We won't all fit in! The tent is too little! It will be fine! In you go! Move further in, Mummy Pig! Daddy, you're too big for the tent!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们不可能都进去的！这个帐篷太小了！不会有问题的！都进去吧。再进去一点，猪妈妈。爸爸，你太胖了进不来的！

yingyinNormal.en: And last night, my tent ripped, so I had to sleep under a plywood board leaning up against a van.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昨晚我的帐篷坏了，所以我不得不靠着一辆面包车睡在一块胶合板下面。

yingyinNormal.en: The tent is full of big wobbly mirrors. Wow, what's happened to my body? Your are wobbly jelly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个帐篷里都是哈哈镜。哇，我的身体怎么了？哈哈，你现在是晃动的果冻。

yingyinNormal.en: It is morning. Daddy! It was lovely and cozy in the tent! Oh. Where's Daddy? Daddy Pig has gone!
yingyinNormal.zh: 天亮了。爸爸！睡在帐篷里面真的好舒服啊！爸爸在哪儿啊？猪爸爸不见了！

yingyinNormal.en: The tent is a bit little. It was big enough for me when I was a boy. But it does look a bit small now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这顶帐篷有点小耶 。我还是小孩子的时候用的现在这么多人确实有点小。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, what's a garden party? It's where grown-ups stand around talking. What a waste for good tent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，花园派对是什么？就是给大人们站着聊天的地方。真是浪费了一个这么好的帐篷。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh! Do these pegs do anything? Of course! I forgot about the pegs! The pegs hold the tent up. There!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些钉子干嘛用的？噢当然了，我把这些钉子全给忘了。用钉子把帐篷支起来了。好了

yingyinNormal.en: What's that? It is a wild animal. Oh. It is a tiny little bird. Come to look at Petro's tent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么声音呢？一定是野兽要来了！啊啊！哦！只是一只小小的鸟飞来参观佩德罗的帐篷。

examination_example.sentence: We sleep in a <highlight>tent</highlight>, cooked over an open fire, and walked a long distance to take the shower and use the bathroom.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们睡在帐篷里，在篝火上做饭，走了很长一段路去洗澡和上厕所。

examination_example.sentence: The market, which was founded in 1979, sets up its <highlight>tents</highlight> every Saturday from 7: 00 am to 1 p.m, rain or shine.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个成立于1979年的市场，每周六早上7：00至下午1：00支起帐篷营业，风雨无阻。

examination_example.sentence: They went up to the mountains and found the perfect place to set up their <highlight>tent</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们上了山，找到了一个搭帐篷的好地方。

examination_example.sentence: He went camping with us and taught us how to put up a <highlight>tent</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他和我们一起去露营，教我们如何搭帐篷。

examination_example.sentence: Arriving at the campsite, we were divided into groups and given a <highlight>tent</highlight>, some food, a map and a compass.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到达营地后，我们被分成几个小组，并得到一顶帐篷、一些食物、一张地图和一个指南针。
